<div class="content_text">

   <p>
      Since its inception period (july 2002) WSC has been implementing microfinance program as its major component. WSC has followed the Grameen Bank Model Propounded by Nobel laurate Prof. Mohammad Yonus of Bangladesh. The aim of the program is to uplift the socio-economic conditions of the poor women. By August, 2011 over 8000 poor women of Kathmandu District have been benifited from this program. The number of women involve in the program is increasing gradually both at rular and urban areas. In total 371 Wome Support microfinance centers have been established in 29 VDCs and two Metropolitan Cities. Microfinance program is operating through five contact offices.

